  "review_sentences": [
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 0,
      "text": "The primary innovation of this paper seems focused towards increasing the generalization of GANs, while also maintaining convergence and preventing mode collapse.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 1,
      "text": "The authors first discuss common pitfalls concerning the generalization capability of discriminators, providing analytical underpinnings for their later experimental results.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 2,
      "text": "Specifically, they address the problem of gradient explosion in discriminators.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 3,
      "text": "The authors then suggest that a zero-centered gradient penalty (0-GP) can be helpful in addressing this issue.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 4,
      "text": "0-GPs are regularly used in GANs, but the authors point out that the purpose is usually to  provide convergence, not to increase generalizability.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 5,
      "text": "Non-zero centered penalties can give a convergence guarantee but, the authors, assert, can allow overfitting.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 6,
      "text": "A 0-GP can give the same guarantees but without allowing overfitting to occur.",
      "suffix": "\n\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_fact",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 7,
      "text": "The authors then verify these assertions through experimentation on synthetic data, as well as MNIST and ImageNet.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_structuring",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-structuring_summary",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 8,
      "text": "My only issue here is that very little information was given about the size of the training sets. Did they use all the samples?",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_experiment",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 9,
      "text": "Some portion? It is not clear from reading. This would be a serious impediment to reproducibility.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_clarity",
      "polarity": "pol_negative"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 10,
      "text": "All in all, however, the authors provide a convincing  combination of analysis and experimentation.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_evaluative",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "pol_positive"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 11,
      "text": "I believe this paper should be accepted into ICLR.",
      "suffix": "\n\n",
      "review_action": "arg_fact",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 12,
      "text": "Note: there is an error on page 9, in Figure 3.",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "arg_request",
      "fine_review_action": "arg-request_typo",
      "aspect": "asp_substance",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
      "sentence_index": 13,
      "text": "The paragraph explanation should list that the authors' 0-GP is figure 3(e).",
      "suffix": "",
      "review_action": "none",
      "fine_review_action": "none",
      "aspect": "none",
      "polarity": "none"
    },
    {
      "review_id": "rJg7SvH5hQ",
